                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>1.	This Agreement is made up of the Pre-Agreement Statement and Quotation, the document recording your electronic or written acceptance of both the Pre-Agreement Statement and Quotation and these terms and conditions. In terms of this Agreement, the Credit Provider agrees to lend me the amount set out in the Quotation/Loan Information section and I agree to repay the Credit Provider the amount set out under Total Repayment of the Quotation/Loan Information section.</b></li>
                        <li>2.	<b><u>Early settlement and early repayments:</u></b> I may settle this Agreement early at any time in terms of sections 122 and 125 of the National Credit Act, 34 of 2005 (“the Act”) by paying the unpaid balance, the unpaid interest and all other fees and charges up to the date of settlement. I may also make early repayments under this Agreement.</li>
                        <li>3.	<b><u>Addresses for receiving documents:</u></b> I nominate the address set out in the Pre-Agreement Statement and Quotation for purposes of communication, including legal notices and court orders. Either party to this Agreement may change its address by delivering to the other party a written notice of the new address by hand, registered mail, or electronic mail.</li>
                        <li>4.	<b><u>Payments under the Agreement:</u></b>  I authorise the Credit Provider to deduct the monthly instalments and other amounts due in terms of this Agreement from my bank account.</li>
                        <li>5.	<b><u>Penalty clause and Legal Costs:</u></b> If I default under this Agreement, I agree that the Credit Provider may charge me penalty interest on arrear instalments at the same interest rate set out in the <b>Quotation/Loan Information section.</b> I agree that all attorneys' or registered debt collectors' costs can be recovered from me on the higher of the attorney and client scale or the published tariff recoverable by registered debt collectors.</li>
                        <li>6.	<b><u>Credit Provider's right to terminate this Agreement:</u></b> The Credit Provider may enforce and/or terminate this Agreement against me if I default with any of the agreed instalments in terms of this Agreement, in terms of sections 123, 129 and 130 of the Act, which may result in a court enforcing the repayment of my outstanding obligations in terms of this Agreement and a judgment against me being recorded at credit bureaus, which will be available to other credit providers.</li>
                        <li>7.	<b><u>Account statements:</u></b> The Credit Provider will provide a free statement to me at the end of every third month and statements during intermediate months will be provided to me on request at a cost computed at the maximum allowable provided for in the Act.</li>
